Fourth Avenue and 27th Street, showing subway construction.

October 19, 1900.

William B. Parsons.

Fourth Avenue, north from 27th Street, showing subway constructions.

February 16, 1901.

William B. Parsons Collection.

Fourth Avenue, west side, north from E. 27th Street, (left) as photographed during constructional period for the Lexington Avenue Subway. At the left appears a portion of the Du St. Esprit French Church. This site is No. 45
E. 27th Street.

January 3, 1901

Fourth Avenue, east side, north from 27th Street. Note shadow of old Madison Square Garden in foreground.
1905[?]
Brown Brothers, Photographers.
West side of Fourth Avenue, facing north from 27th Street. Part of old Madison Square Garden at left. 1906. Brown Brothers, Photographers. NO REPRODUCTIONS.

4th Avenue.  27th Street to 28th

President, Borough of Manhattan  March 21, 1920

Fourth Ave, west side, south from and including 27th Street, showing a rear view of the old Madison Square Garden.

August 13, 1924

Eugene L. Armbruster, Collection.

East 27th Street, south side, west from and including Fourth Ave. The view showing the north side of the old Madison Square Garden.

August 3, 1924

Eugene L. Armbruster, Collection.

East 27th Street, at, adjoining and west of N.W. corner of the Fourth Ave.  Shown at No. 45, is the Du. St. Esprit French Church.

About 1926.

MAY BE REPRODUCED.

East 27th Street, at Fourth Ave., as seen thru the S.W. corner of clearance on the former site of the old Madison Square Garden. Note the Du St. Esprit Church (No. 45), just west of Fourth Ave.

July 9, 1926

F.L. Sperr

(1)
East 27th Street, north side, west from, but not including Fourth to and including Madison Aves., as seen across clearance on the site of the old Madison Square Garden.  On the right, appears at No. 45, the Du St. Esprit French Church.

July 9, 1926.

P. L. Sperr.

The same, showing a complete view of the Du St. Esprit French Church, which is just west of Fourth Ave.
